A *very* rough'n'ready Rails plugin that allows relatively trivial integration of the Protovis ( http://vis.stanford.edu/protovis/ ) javascript
chart rendering API into a Rails project.

The usage is relatively simple, install it as a git submodule:
	git submodule add git://github.com/ciaranj/redmine.git vendor/plugins/protovisonrails
	
There is an includes helper ( protovis_includes ) that allows you to automatically pull in these javascript files.

This initial stab at a plugin requires that width/height parameters are passed in as well as block of javascript that allows
configuration of the particular chart.  Currently this looks similar to the following:


   my_js= <<eos
             add(pv.Rule)
                .data(function() pv.range(0, 2, .5))
                .bottom(function(d) d * 70)
                .anchor("left").add(pv.Label)
              .root.add(pv.Bar)
                .data([1, 1.2, 1.7, 1.5, .7])
                .height(function(d) d * 70).width(20)
                .bottom(0).left(function() this.index * 25 + 4)
eos                .anchor("bottom").add(pv.Label)
  
	chart_raw_js(800, 600, my_js)
	
The intention is to provide more of a useful object model to build these objects up programatically.